vulnerability.name: USN-3702-2
vulnerability.description: USN-3702-1 fixed a vulnerability in PHP. PHP 7.2.7 did not actually include the fix for CVE-2018-12882. This update adds a backported patch to correct the issue.  We apologize for the inconvenience.  Original advisory details:   It was discovered that PHP incorrectly handled exif tags in certain images.  A remote attacker could use this issue to cause PHP to crash, resulting in  a denial of service, or possibly execute arbitrary code.

statements.status_notes: PHP could be made to crash or run programs if it opened a specially crafted file.
